      "sourceRef": "kontourai-flow-agents-288/evidence.json",
      "excerptOrSummary": "Manual scratch-root probes: (a) F8 CLI orphan heartbeat/release die() nonzero+remediation with no stream write, claim->heartbeat->release succeeds; maybeEmitHeartbeat on a heartbeat-only (no-claim) stream skips reason=no-claim without mutating the stream. (b) F1: renaming liveness-policy.js makes init-plan exit 0 with one stderr diagnostic naming the missing module and writes no claim; file restored and git status verified back to the original untracked state. (c) Zero-env-config lifecycle emits claim+heartbeat+release (default-on); FLOW_AGENTS_LIVENESS=off and off+U+200B both produce zero events across the same lifecycle. (d) FLOW_AGENTS_LIVENESS_TTL_SECONDS=300 -> ttlSeconds:300 on the claim; custom throttle=10s -> 9s throttled, 11s emits, with injected now. (e) TTL=300 with tool-activity heartbeats every 100s keeps the holder held at T0+301s; without activity the same claim goes free at T0+301s. (f) Hostile ANSI/newline active_slug is sanitized before being used as the emitted heartbeat subjectId (raw ESC/newline bytes never appear in the stream); CLI liveness status/claim strip control chars from terminal display while the persisted event retains the raw value for data fidelity.",
